name: DOCS_RCVD_OB_HX
description: This table contains OB History information received from other organizations.

columns.name: DOCUMENT_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier (.1 item) for the document record.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE_REAL
columns.description: A unique contact date in decimal format. The integer portion of the number indicates the date of contact. The digits after the decimal distinguish different contacts on the same date and are unique for each contact on that date. For example, .00 is the first/only contact, .01 is the second contact, etc.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this contact. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this contact.

columns.name: ADOPTION_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: Adoption type for this delivery.

columns.name: ADOPTION_TYPE_NAME
columns.description: Category title for the adoption type for this delivery from the source environment.

columns.name: ANTENAT_STEROIDS_C_NAME
columns.description: Antenatal steroids given.

columns.name: CORD_CLAMP_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Instant when the cord was clamped.

columns.name: DILA_COMPL_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Instant when dilation completed.

columns.name: FORCEPS_ATTEMPTED_YN
columns.description: Whether delivery by forceps was attempted.

columns.name: LABOR_ATTEMPTED_YN
columns.description: Whether a trial of labor was attempted.

columns.name: LABOR_ST_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Instant when labor began.

columns.name: LABOR_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The type of labor for this birth.

columns.name: LIVING_STAT_BIRTH_C_NAME
columns.description: Living status of the baby at birth.

columns.name: PLAC_DEL_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Instant when the placenta was delivered.

columns.name: LIV_STAT_BIRTH_NAME
columns.description: Category title for the living status of the baby at birth from the source environment.

columns.name: PUSH_START_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Instant when pushing began.

columns.name: RUPTURE_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Instant when rupture of membranes occurred.

columns.name: RUPT_2_DEL_SEC
columns.description: Time from rupture of membranes to delivery in seconds.

columns.name: SKIN_2_SK_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Instant when skin to skin was initiated.

columns.name: VAC_ATTEMPTED_YN
columns.description: Whether delivery by vacuum was attempted.

columns.name: MOM_DEL_ENC_IDENT
columns.description: Maternal delivery encounter associated with the birth.

columns.name: BABY_DEL_ENC_IDENT
columns.description: Newborn delivery encounter associated with the birth.

columns.name: MOTHER_ARR_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Instant when the mother arrived at labor and delivery.

columns.name: CERV_RIPE_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Cervical ripening instant for this delivery.

columns.name: PREGRAVID_WEIGHT
columns.description: Pregravid weight for this delivery.

columns.name: PLAN_DEL_MTHD_C_NAME
columns.description: Planned delivery method for this delivery.

columns.name: PLAN_DEL_MTHD_NAME_STR
columns.description: Category title for the planned delivery method from the source environment.

columns.name: BABY_LINK_PAT_ID
columns.description: The link to the baby that was born.
